* She tensed as Prowl came closer to her, but noting the concern in his 
eyes.
But she pulls her head away as he tries to pat her head, only pacing in a 
wider circle around the room.

Though, didn't he understand? How she couldn't possably know how to 
transform or even speak?
It was impossable to communicate to him that she needed his help, not his 
verble selutions.

All he needed to do was scan her, that was it. Then he would know just what 
was going on, that her beast modes had screwed up all of her main systems.

But, even as she thought this, the rage and bloodlust of her modes was 
building. And she could feel her addrenalin rising, and that was 
bad...really bad.

She stopped and simply stayed there with her head bowed a bit, looking 
towards Prowl and simply watching him...still mewing softly.
However, almost every mew sounded as if she were saying Help Me.
And if she didn't get out of this mode soon, there wouldn't be a thing in 
this world that could help her then.*
